  "target_response": {
    "text": "A recovery score is a composite: it compares this morning's HRV, resting heart rate, and sleep against your own recent norms and compresses them into one 0-100 number. Mid-band values like today's 56% mean the inputs disagree, so the score alone can't hand you a verdict — the inputs can. Your HRV of 61 ms is a touch under your 30-day baseline of 63.8 ms, well inside its usual spread of 5.2 ms; your resting heart rate of 55 bpm sits within a beat of its 54.2 mean; the real drag is sleep, 6.7 h against a 7.5 h need. Read together: capacity for quality work is probably there, with sleep as the caveat. One more thing — the score itself is graded medium confidence today, so lean on the inputs rather than the headline number.",
